            "description": "A light moment involving Salman Naseer and Babar Azam went viral after Peshawar Zalmi’s win over Quetta Gladiators, with the PSL CEO seen performing a gesture to ward off the ‘evil eye’ for the Zalmi captain.Meanwhile, on the field, Peshawar Zalmi extended their lead at the top of the table and strengthened their position with an eight-wicket win over Quetta Gladiators at the National Bank Stadium on Wednesday, moving closer to playoff qualification. Watch Why Pakistan don't trust Babar Azam any more | T20 World Cup 2026 After being asked to field first, Zalmi bowlers, led by Sufiyan Muqeem and Iftikhar Ahmed, restricted Quetta Gladiators to 154 all out in 20 overs, with limited contributions from the batting line-up.In response, Zalmi chased down the 155-run target with nine balls to spare, losing just two wickets."
